Request types:
	Head Server:
			-> Send a new file
			-> Retrieve file
			-> Delete a file
			-> create a clone header file
			-> Attach a new cluster server
			-> New cluster server replacing the old broken one
			-> Replicate the head server
			-> Take the position of primary head server
			-* Exit the server name space if the servers aren't responding
			-> Health check the cluster server 
			-> Remove the cluster server if it's not responding
	Cluster Server:
			-> Delete the chunks at Request
			-> Store and restore the file on Request
			-> Send health signals to head server 
			-> Check the chunks hashses after writing any bit to the drive

	Zookeeper : 
			-> Health check the primary head server 
			-> Replace the primary head server if it crashes ( using some sort of voting system)
			-> Also done the health check for the cluster server
		

